The column itself was still active though....
This had the effect of stopping any additions or saves from happening to the table.
Reinstated commented out code.
.head 7 -  ! 14/08/2003 (PXD) The problem now exists where this column and the colTreeTypeDesc column are duplicating
the same information. This is causing grief when performing the Order By' options. I have replaced all references 
to this column colTypeDesc with colTreeTypeDesc and completely commented out this column
.head 7 -  ! 01/09/2003 (PXD) colTypeDesc is required for printing on the invoices and such. It does not show '2nds' and other details
in the text, where Tree_Type_Desc does show these details, and is required for internal use.
I have re-instated the column, and references, but removed the option to do 'order by', as well as others that are not req'd.
