.head 4 +  Functions 
.head 5 +  Function: fnSaveChanges
.head 6 -  Description: Saves all changes in the table window including rows edited, new rows
and rows which are marked for deletion. It returns TRUE or FALSE to 
indicate success or failure
.head 6 +  Returns 
.head 7 -  Boolean: 
.head 6 -  Parameters 
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Sql Handle: hSqlSave
.head 7 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  Call SalWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 7 +  If SqlConnect( hSqlSave )
.head 8 -  ! First of all do deletes
.head 8 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 8 +  If NOT fnDoChanges ( hSqlSave, 
"
DELETE
	FROM
	Customer_Item
WHERE
	ROWID = :hWndForm.colRowId
", ROW_MarkDeleted, ROW_New ) 
.head 9 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 8 -  ! Do inserts
.head 8 +  If bOk
.head 9 +  If NOT fnDoChanges ( hSqlSave,
"
INSERT 
	INTO
	Customer_Item (
		Cust_No,
		Supplier_Id,
		Stock_Item_No,
		Fine_line,
		Retail_Price,
		Barcode ) 
VALUES ( 
	:dlgFinelineMaintenance.npCustomerNo,
	:dlgFinelineMaintenance.sSupplierId,
	:colnStockItemNo,
	:colnFinelineNo,
	:colnRetailPrice,
	:colsBarCode 
	) 
", ROW_New, ROW_MarkDeleted ) 
.head 10 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 8 -  ! Do updates
.head 8 +  If bOk 
.head 9 +  If NOT fnDoChanges ( hSqlSave, 
"
UPDATE
	Customer_Item
SET
	Fine_line 		= :colnFinelineNo,
	Retail_Price 	= :colnRetailPrice,
	Barcode 		= :colsBarCode
WHERE
	RowId 		= :colRowId
" , ROW_Edited, ROW_New | ROW_MarkDeleted )  
.head 10 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 8 -  ! If everything is still Ok commit changes and repopulate table to refresh row flags etc
.head 8 -  ! else rollback all changes which may have been made but had errors.
.head 8 +  If bOk 
.head 9 -  Call SqlCommit ( hSqlSave ) 
.head 9 -  Call SalSendMsg( hWndForm, PAM_POPULATE, 0, 0 )
.head 8 +  Else 
.head 9 -  Call SqlPrepareAndExecute( hSqlSave, 'ROLLBACK' )
.head 9 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'Save changes failed. Try again later', 'Changes not saved', MB_Ok | MB_IconExclamation )
.head 7 -  Call SalWaitCursor( FALSE)
.head 7 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  Function: fnDoChanges
.head 6 -  Description: This function take as a parameter the type of rows 
it is looking for ( eg. New, Edited, MarkDeleted ).  It also takes 
an sql statement that is used with the sqlexecute ( ).
.head 6 +  Returns 
.head 7 -  Boolean: 
.head 6 +  Parameters 
.head 7 -  Sql Handle: hSqlpDatabase
.head 7 -  String: spSqlStmt
.head 7 -  Number: npFlagsOn
.head 7 -  Number: npFlagsOff
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Number: nCurrentRow
.head 7 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 7 -  Set nCurrentRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 7 +  If SalTblAnyRows( hWndForm, npFlagsOn, npFlagsOff)
.head 8 -  Call SqlPrepare( hSqlpDatabase, spSqlStmt)
.head 8 +  While SalTblFindNextRow( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, npFlagsOn, npFlagsOff) AND  bOk
.head 9 -  Call SalTblSetContext( hWndForm, nCurrentRow )
.head 9 +  When SqlError
.head 10 +  If SalNumberLow ( lParam )  = nSQLError_UniqueViolation
.head 11 -  Call SalMessageBox ( 
'The stock item - ' || colsItemDescription || ' is already an item with this customer.
This row will not be inserted into the database', 'Unique Value Problem', MB_Ok | MB_IconExclamation ) 
.head 11 -  Return TRUE
.head 9 +  If NOT SqlExecute ( hSqlpDatabase )
.head 10 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 7 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  Function: fnMarkDeleted
.head 6 -  Description: This function first checks to ensure that at least one row is selected
If not is displays and error message
If so then it goes through one by one checking each selected row to see
if the ROW_MarkDeleted flag is already set. If it is then it deselects , otherwise selects.
.head 6 -  Returns 
.head 6 -  Parameters 
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 7 -  Number: nCurrentRow
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 7 +  If NOT SalTblAnyRows( hWndForm, ROW_Selected, 0 )
.head 8 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'No rows selected', 'Mark for deletion', MB_Ok | MB_IconExclamation )
.head 8 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 7 +  Else 
.head 8 -  Set nCurrentRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 8 +  While SalTblFindNextRow( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, ROW_Selected, 0 )
.head 9 +  If SalTblQueryRowFlags( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, ROW_New )
.head 10 -  Call SalTblDeleteRow( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, TBL_NoAdjust )
.head 10 -  Set nCurrentRow = nCurrentRow - 1
.head 9 +  Else If SalTblQueryRowFlags( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, ROW_MarkDeleted )
.head 10 -  Call SalTblSetRowFlags( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, ROW_MarkDeleted, FALSE )
.head 9 +  Else 
.head 10 -  Call SalTblSetRowFlags( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, ROW_MarkDeleted, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  ! Function: fnAddNewRow
.head 6 -  Description: This function is called to create a new row in the table and
then initalise the row with data from global vars
.head 6 -  Returns 
.head 6 +  Parameters 
.head 7 -  Receive Number: npNewRow
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Number: nNewRow
.head 7 -  Number: nCount
.head 7 -  Number: nTmp
.head 7 -  String: sTmp
.head 7 -  Number: nRowsLowerHalf
.head 7 -  Boolean: bAdjust
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  ! Insert new row in table
.head 7 -  ! Need to get a number of things off the stack before information we are interested in is 'popped'
.head 7 -  ! Call PopNumber( Number, Boolean )
.head 7 -  ! To get the stock item no I need to pop all bar the top one
.head 7 -  Set npNewRow =  SalSendMsg ( hWndForm, PAM_ADDROW, 0, 0 ) 
.head 7 -  Set nCount = 0
.head 7 +  While nCount < 3
.head 8 -  Call PopNumber ( nTmp, TRUE ) 
.head 8 -  Set nCount = nCount + 1
.head 7 -  Call PopNumber ( colnStockItemNo, TRUE ) 
.head 7 -  ! Only one pop is required to get the tree type description 
.head 7 -  Call PopString ( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString ( colsTreeType, TRUE ) 
.head 7 -  ! One more pop required prior to getting the item description
.head 7 -  Call PopString ( sTmp, TRUE ) 
.head 7 -  Call PopString ( colsItemDescription, TRUE ) 
.head 7 -  Return TRUE
.head 5 +  Function: fnAddNewRow
.head 6 -  Description: This function is called to create a new row in the table and
then initalise the row with data from global vars
.head 6 +  Returns 
.head 7 -  Boolean: 
.head 6 +  Parameters 
.head 7 -  Receive Number: npNewRow
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Number: nNewRow
.head 7 -  Number: nCount
.head 7 -  Number: nTmp
.head 7 -  String: sTmp
.head 7 -  Number: nRowsLowerHalf
.head 7 -  Boolean: bAdjust
.head 7 -  String: sNewTreeType
.head 7 -  String: sNewItemDescription
.head 7 -  Number: nNewStockItemNo
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  ! Insert new row in table
.head 7 -  ! Need to get a number of things off the stack before information we are interested in is 'popped'
.head 7 -  ! Call PopNumber( Number, Boolean )
.head 7 -  ! To get the stock item no I need to pop all bar the top one
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopNumber( nTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopNumber( nTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sNewTreeType, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sNewItemDescription, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopString( sTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopNumber( nTmp, TRUE )
.head 7 -  Call PopNumber( nNewStockItemNo, TRUE )
.head 7 +  If fnCheckDuplicateItem( hSqlDetail, npCustomerNo, nNewStockItemNo, sSupplierId )
.head 8 -  Call SalMessageBox( colsTreeType || ' ' || colsItemDescription || ' already exists.  Please select another.', 'Warning', MB_Ok )
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 +  Else 
.head 8 -  Set npNewRow =  SalSendMsg ( hWndForm, PAM_ADDROW, 0, 0 ) 
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 -  Set colsTreeType = sNewTreeType
.head 8 -  Set colsItemDescription = sNewItemDescription
.head 8 -  Set colnStockItemNo = nNewStockItemNo
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 -  Call SalSetFocus( colnFinelineNo )
.head 8 -  Return TRUE
.head 5 +  Function: fnSearch
.head 6 -  Description: This function searches the table window for the text that the user has entered.
If it finds a row that matches, it scrolls to it and highlights the row.  
If it reaches the end of the table and no more matches have been found it advises the user no rows match their data entry.
.head 6 +  Returns 
.head 7 -  Boolean: 
.head 6 +  Parameters 
.head 7 -  Number: npSearchMethod
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Boolean: bRowFound
.head 7 -  Number: nCurrentRow
.head 7 -  String: sConvertedEntry ! Uppercase conversion of users entry
.head 7 -  ! ! used to find out which row they are on right now, so 
that if no rows are found the context can be set back to the original row.
.head 7 -  Number: nContextRowNow
.head 7 -  Number: nResult
.head 7 -  Number: nOffset
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  ! First find out where we are right now
.head 7 -  Set nContextRowNow = SalTblQueryContext ( hWndForm ) 
.head 7 -  ! Next convert the user entry to uppercase
.head 7 -  Set sConvertedEntry = SalStrUpperX( dfsSearch )
.head 7 -  ! Now search either up or down depending on which radio button has been pressed.
.head 7 -  Set nCurrentRow = nContextRowNow
.head 7 +  Loop 
.head 8 +  If npSearchMethod = nSEARCH_DOWN
.head 9 -  Set nCurrentRow = nCurrentRow + 1
.head 8 +  Else 
.head 9 -  Set nCurrentRow = nCurrentRow - 1
.head 8 -  Set nResult = SalTblFetchRow( hWndForm, nCurrentRow)
.head 8 +  If nResult = TBL_RowFetched
.head 9 -  ! If the row is fetched compare the item description with the user entry
.head 9 -  ! If there is a match somewhere in the string then we set the focus to that row and highlight the match
.head 9 -  Set nOffset = SalStrScan ( SalStrUpperX ( colsItemDescription ), sConvertedEntry )
.head 9 +  If nOffset >= 0 
.head 10 -  Call SalTblSetFlagsAnyRows ( hWndForm, ROW_Selected, FALSE, ROW_Selected, 0 ) 
.head 10 -  Call SalTblSetFocusCell( hWndForm, nCurrentRow, colsItemDescription, nOffset, SalStrLength ( sConvertedEntry )  )
.head 10 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 10 -  Break 
.head 8 +  Else If nResult = TBL_NoMoreRows
.head 9 -  Call SalMessageBox ( 'No matches found', 'Search Result', MB_IconExclamation | MB_Ok )
.head 9 -  Call SalTblSetContext ( hWndForm, nContextRowNow ) 
.head 9 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 9 -  Break 
.head 7 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  Function: fnCheckDuplicateItem
.head 6 -  Description: 
.head 6 +  Returns 
.head 7 -  Boolean: 
.head 6 +  Parameters 
.head 7 -  Sql Handle: hSqlHandle
.head 7 -  Number: nCustNo
.head 7 -  Number: nStockItemNo
.head 7 -  String: sSupplierId
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  String: sSql
.head 7 -  Number: nInd
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  Set sSql = " SELECT 
    1
 FROM 
    Customer_Item
 WHERE 
    Cust_No = :nCustNo AND 
    Stock_Item_No = :nStockItemNo and
	Supplier_Id = :sSupplierId"
.head 7 +  If SqlPrepareAndExecute( hSqlHandle, sSql ) AND SqlFetchNext( hSqlHandle, nInd )
.head 8 -  Return TRUE
.head 7 +  Else 
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 +  Function: fnPrintBarcodes
.head 6 -  Description: This function will print a desired number of fineline item barcodes for a selected item
.head 6 -  Returns 
.head 6 -  Parameters 
.head 6 -  Static Variables 
.head 6 +  Local variables 
.head 7 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 7 -  Number: nCurrentRow
.head 7 -  ! String: sReportVars
.head 7 -  ! String: sReportInto
.head 7 -  String: sFineline
.head 7 -  String: sSupplier
.head 6 +  Actions 
.head 7 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 7 +  If NOT SalTblAnyRows( hWndForm, ROW_Selected, 0 )
.head 8 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'No row selected', 'Print Fineline Barcodes', MB_Ok | MB_IconExclamation )
